      • processRental

        void processRental()
        Rent the next available car to the first waiting customer

      • processReturn

        void processReturn(boolean problem)
        Process the return of a rented car. Processing depends upon whether a problem was reported or not. The car returned is the one at the front of the queue of rented cars.
        Parameters:
        problem - true if a problem was reported, false otherwise.

      • processDetailed

        void processDetailed()
        Process a car that was out for detailing and make it available. The car processed is the one at the front of the detail shop queue.

      • processRepaired

        void processRepaired()
        Process a car that was out for repair and send it for detailing. The car processed is the one at the front of the repair shop queue.

      • processNewCar

        void processNewCar(java.lang.String id,
                   java.lang.String make,
                   java.lang.String model,
                   java.lang.String color)
        Add a new car to the inventory of cars, making it available for renting.
        Parameters:
        id - the fleet number for the new car
        make - the make of the new car
        model - the model of the new car
        color - the color of the new car
        Throws:
        InvalidIDException - if the fleet number for the car is invalid.
